BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Ug3dcbsCHaN1NdJNfLC_o
SUMMARY:Samantha Yun Wall: What We Leave Behind
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260214T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Samantha Yun Wall’s new paintings use overlapping silhouettes o
	f female figures as portals to unknown spaces and different temporal realm
	s. Impetus for the new body of work is a Korean folk tale in which the Pas
	que flower is symbolic of a grandmother who passed away without the loving
	 care of her grandchildren. It is a story of melancholy\, loss\, and remem
	brance. The delicate hair on the flower’s stem differentiates it\, and the
	 artist gives the plant a surreal aspect in some of her paintings\, replac
	ing the flower’s center with a watchful eye.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cul
	ture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/samantha-yun-wall-what-we
	-leave-behind/18026187/2026-02-14T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:tnWRAWyedkk06IAUaXxPv
SUMMARY:Call To Conscience Museum Opening Ceremony
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260214T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Call To Conscience Museum Opening Ceremony       Friday\, Febru
	ary 14th | 10:00 AM - 11:00 AM       Celebrating the 100th Anniversary of 
	Black History Month      Join us for the grand opening of the  Call To Con
	science Black History Month Museum  at the historic Columbia City Theater!
	      This year\, we celebrate 100 years since Dr. Carter G. Woodson began
	 Negro History Week in February 1926.      Featured Exhibits:             
	  ✦ The Seattle Chapter of the Black Panther Party          ✦ The Hartsfie
	ld Enslaved Quilt Collection          ✦ The History of Religion in Seattle
	's Black Communities          ✦ Jackson Street Jazz \\(including Quincy Jo
	nes legacy\\)          ✦ A History of Black Tacoma \\(presented by T. Hear
	d\\)          ✦ BlackPast.org and Dr. Quintard Taylor Exhibit          ✦ R
	ainier Cinema Vintage Black Movie Poster Collection          ✦ History of 
	Black Athletes in the Metro League            FREE ADMISSION  - All welcom
	e!      Museum tours will follow the opening ceremony.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - 
	Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/call-to-conscience-museum
	-opening-ceremony/17897760/2026-02-14T00
LOCATION:Columbia City Theater\, 4916 Rainer Ave. S.\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
