BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:xeI0DqmFRKVPQ-K7rmglf
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260222T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cu
	lture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-02-22T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:-bYmOgNaiyj3p9QQ5scim
SUMMARY:UGAs + Stage Workers Week
DTSTAMP:20260214T003622Z
DTSTART:20260223T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Theatre Puget Sound is thrilled to share that the 2026 Unified 
	General Auditions are right around the corner - with new and improved elem
	ents for 2026!  What are the UGAs \\+ Stage Workers Week?  Last year\, TPS
	 introduced the Tech & Design Job Fair and Playwright Pitches for the firs
	t time. As we work to expand and grow our resources for our diverse member
	ship base\, we're expanding even more. This week will include 4 days of Un
	ified General Auditions\, 1 morning dedicated to Playwright Pitches\, and 
	an afternoon dedicated to designer\, director\, choreographer and stage wo
	rker presentations.   Theatre Puget Sound is proud to produce a full week 
	of events and services to help strengthen\, grow and connect our performin
	g arts community! More details and important dates below. More information
	 on registration\, requirements\, and how to get involved coming soon. Mar
	k your calendars and start prepping!  ️\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/ugas-stage-workers-week/1
	7738970/2026-02-23T00
LOCATION:Book-It Repertory Theatre\, 305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
